The paper discusses the similarities and differences between blockchain systems and traditional database systems, and proposes improvements to the transaction pipeline of Hyperledger Fabric by transitioning well-understood database concepts to the blockchain system. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DB (Databases), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
